<h1>Examples</h1>

<section>
	<p class="example-intro">Awkward construction occurs whenever the structure of a sentence confuses the meaning or makes the sentence less readable. There are many different causes of awkward construction, and awkward construction can occur even in sentences with perfect punctuation.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h4 class="example example-sentence example-example">Clinical decision support systems help healthcare providers connect to research-based knowledge, increasing the quality of care, and they can provide alarms and alerts, reducing the risk of error.<span class="red">AWKWARD!</span></h4>
	<p class="example example-explanation example-explanation">This sentence is awkward because of the over-use of commas and clumsy grouping.</p>
	<h4 class="example example-corrected example-corrected">Clinical decision support systems help healthcare providers connect to research-based knowledge and provide alarms and alerts, increasing the quality of care and reducing the risk of error.<span class="green">BETTER!</span></h4>
	<p class="example corrected-explanation example-corrected-explanation">To correct the awkward construction, we group our items based on their role in the sentence. Remember, with awkward construction there is often more than one way to fix the problem. Here, we also could have replaced the comma before "and they can provide alarms and alerts" with a semicolon.</p>
